The '''Arulmiku Sivan Temple''' is a [[Hindu temple]] located in the [[Municipalities of the canton of Zürich|municipality]] of [[Glattbrugg]] in the [[Canton of Zürich]] in [[Switzerland]]. [[File:Glattbrugg Sivan Kovil 20170610 152530.jpg|thumb|upright|Entrance of the renewed building in June 2017]]
== History == In the 1990s, an interreligious society was established in the canton of Zürich to support the foundation of a centre for spiritual and cultural care of [[Tamil people]] in Switzerland, as well as to preserve and maintain the [[Tamil culture]] of the approximatively 35,000 (around 20,000 in the canton of Zürich) Tamil people of [[Sri Lanka]]n origin living in Switzerland. So, the [[Sri Sivasubramaniar Temple]] in Adliswil and the Arulmiku Sivan Temple in Glattbrugg were founded in 1994 as a [[Foundation (nonprofit organization)|non-profit foundation]].<ref name="religionench">{{cite web|url=http://www.religionenschweiz.ch/hinduismus.html |title=Hinduismus in der Schweiz |publisher=Religionen in der Schweiz |author= |language=German |date= |accessdate=2015-03-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215200913/http://religionenschweiz.ch/hinduismus.html |archivedate=2015-02-15 }}</ref> While some 5,000 Indian Hindus in Switzerland founded their own cultural associations, but not a temple, the Tamil Hindus opened 19 houses of worship since the 1990s.
== Location == The temple was established in a pre-existing warehouse at the industry quarter between Glattbrugg and [[Seebach (Zürich)]]. The Temple is located at Industriestrasse 34, 8152 Glattbrugg.<ref name="kontakt">{{cite web|url=http://www.sivankovil.ch/?pn=contact_de|title=Kontakt|publisher=sivankovil.ch|author=|language=German, Tamil|date=|accessdate=2015-03-20}}</ref>
== Cultural and religious life == ''[[Puja (Hinduism)|Poojas]]'' are celebrated twice per day,<ref name="öffnungszeiten">{{cite web|url=http://www.sivankovil.ch/?pn=Open_time|title=Öffnungszeiten|publisher=sivankovil.ch|author=|language=German, Tamil|date=|accessdate=2015-03-20}}</ref> and the temple festivals attract up to 4,000 devotees and visitors.<ref name="zul-20120702">{{cite web|url=http://www.zuonline.ch/artikel_72063.html |title=Umzug zu Ehren der Götter |publisher=[[Zürcher Unterländer]] |author=Simone Thommen Awe |language=German |date=2012-07-02 |accessdate=2015-03-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402123751/http://www.zuonline.ch/artikel_72063.html |archivedate=2015-04-02 }}</ref>
