'''South Sudanese Canadians''' are [[Canadians|Canadian]] of [[South Sudan]]ese [[ancestry]] or a South Sudanese who has [[Canadian citizenship]]. South Sudanese Canadians can also include children born in Canada to a Canadian parent and South Sudanese parent. South Sudanese Canadians emigrated to the Canada in the 1980s and 1990s as refugees from [[Second Sudanese Civil War]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/sudanese-canadians-return-to-heal-their-shattered-homeland/article1214023/|title=Sudanese Canadians return to heal their shattered homeland|first=Geoffrey|last=York|work=The Globe and Mail|date=26 September 2010|accessdate=7 August 2016}}</ref>
