'''The Raven''' is involved with [[Web television]], [[Internet radio]], and [[Citizen journalism]].<ref>[http://www.ojr.org/ojr/workplace/1060223904.php University of Southern California's Online Journalism Review. August 7 2003. Personal Broadcasting Opens Yet Another Front For Journalists]</ref><ref>[http://www.dailywireless.org/2003/08/08/daytonabeach-live/ Daily Wireless. August 11 2003]</ref><ref>[http://paulding.com/forum/index.php/topic/340-is-paulding-com-the-first-to-do-the-tv-thing/ Paulding. October 30, 2003]</ref><ref>[http://justacrazyjournalist.blogspot.com/ Blogging versus Journalism. December 5 2004]</ref><ref>[http://www.socialmedia.biz/2004/08/08/leading-the-video-blog-revolution/ Social Media. August 8 2004]</ref><ref name="amazon">[https://www.amazon.com/Darknet-Hollywoods-Against-Digital-Generation/dp/0471683345/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1338078728&sr=8-1 Darknet Hollywood's War against the Digital Generation. Chapter 8. 2005. J.D. Lasica]</ref><ref>[http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2005/10/28/EBG72FCAQE1.DTL&ao=all San Francisco Chronicle. October 28 2005. Underworld's Darknet foments copyright revolution against hollywood]</ref> The Raven claims to have reported on Daytona Beach events via video broadcasts through a Web TV station as far back as 2000.

==History==
* 1998: The Raven started and ran [[Albuquerque, New Mexico|Albuquerque's]] first [[Internet radio]] station "Route 66 LIVE".<ref>[http://www.accessmylibrary.com/article-1G1-108359806/n-e-heights-man.html  Albuquerque Tribune]</ref>
* 2000: The Raven started Daytona Beach Live.<ref>[http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=NJ&p_theme=nj&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_text_search-0=%22broadcasting%20on%20a%20shoestring%22&p_field_label-0=Author&s_dispstring=broadcasting%20on%20a%20shoestring%20AND%20date Daytona Beach News-Journal; May 20 2002; Page 01A; Broadcasting on a shoestring]</ref><ref>[http://makemoneyblogging.com/blog/a-one-man-media-empire One Man Media Empire]</ref><ref>[http://www.ojr.org/ojr/workplace/1060217106.php University of Southern California Online Journalism Review. August 8 2003. What is Participatory Journalism]</ref> The station showed video about life, events, and attractions in the Daytona Beach area <ref>[https://www.amazon.com/Darknet-Hollywoods-Against-Digital-Generation/dp/0471683345/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1338078728&sr=8-1  2005 Darknet: Hollywood's War Against the Digital Generation, chapter 8]</ref> for the 17,000 viewers.<ref>[http://www.newmediajournalism.aut.ac.nz/archive/2004/seminars/rqp4512.htm 2004 Aucklan University of Technology's New Media Gazette]</ref> Events included the [[Daytona Beach Bike Week]],<ref>[http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=NJ&p_theme=nj&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_text_search-0=Harold%20AND%20Kionka&p_field_label-0=Author&s_dispstring=Harold%20Kionka%20AND%20date(all)&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&xcal_useweights=no Daytona Beach News Journal. March 3 2004. Page 03C. Bike fest attracts movie makers]</ref><ref>[http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=NJ&p_theme=nj&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_text_search-0=Biketoberfest%20AND%20action%20AND%20live&p_field_label-0=Author&s_dispstring=Biketoberfest%20action%20live%20AND%20date(nj02)&p_field_date-0=YMD_date&p_params_date-0=date:B,E&p_text_date-0=nj02&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&xcal_useweights=no Daytona Beach News Journal; October 18 2002; Page 01C; Main Street Action Live On Internet]</ref><ref>[http://www.bikernet.com/pages/story_detail.aspx?id=4990 Biker Net; March 4 2004; Page 3]</ref> hurricanes,<ref>[http://www.dslreports.com/forum/remark,11245498 2004 Broadband DSL Reports]</ref><ref>[http://www.socialmedia.biz/2004/08/15/hurricane-charley-up-close/ Social Media. August 15 2004. Hurricane Charley Up Close]</ref> Birthplace of Speed, Black College Reunion, Great Race, Florida International Festival, Biketoberfest, Spaceshuttle launches, Power Boat Races, Rock Bands, and more.<ref>[http://www.ojr.org/ojr/workplace/1060223904.php University of Southern California's Online Journalism Review. August 7 2003. Personal Broadcasting Opens Yet Another Front for Journalists]</ref>
* 2003: The Raven launched Galaxy Universe TV to provide live streaming video overlooking the beach on South Atlantic Avenue <ref>[http://www.dailywireless.org/2003/08/08/daytonabeach-live/ 2003 Daily Wireless]</ref>
*2004: The Raven simulcast across a network of three Internet TV stations for the 2004 [[Biketoberfest]].<ref>[http://www.darknet.com/2004/10/adventures_in_i.html Darknet: Adventures in Internet TV. October 21 2004]</ref>
* 2005: The Raven was featured in Chapter # 8, of the book,  "[[DARKNET Hollywoods War against the Digital Generation]]" <ref name="amazon" />
* 2008: The Raven relocated to [[Adrian, Michigan]] and formed the existing Internet TV stations into the Raven World Communications.<ref>[http://www.ravenworldcommunications.com  RWC]</ref> He continues to report on local events in Adrian.

