{{Infobox Ethnic group | group = Turks in Kyrgyzstan | image = | caption = | popplace = {{hlist|[[Bishkek]] | [[Chuskaya]] | [[Fergana]] | [[Osh]] | [[Talas Province|Talas]]}} | langs = [[Turkish language|Turkish]] | rels = [[Islam]] |population={{Plainlist| * 50,000<ref>{{cite web |author=IRIN Asia|title=KYRGYZSTAN: Focus on Mesketian Turks |url=http://www.irinnews.org/Report.aspx?ReportId=28663|accessdate=2009-10-15}}</ref> to 70,000<ref>{{Harvnb|Blacklock|2005|loc=10}}.</ref> * plus 3,200 Turkish nationals<ref>{{Harvnb|Council of Europe|2007|loc=130}}.</ref> }}}}
'''Turks in Kyrgyzstan''' are ethnic [[Turkish people|Turks]] who live in [[Kyrgyzstan]].
== History == The majority of [[Turkish people|Turks]] were deported from [[Meskheti|south-western Georgia]] to [[Central Asia]] in 1944, where they were employed largely in the agricultural sector in grain and livestock production. Of the 207,500 Meskhetian Turks registered in the [[Soviet Census (1989)|1989 Soviet census]], there were 21,294 [[Turkish people|Turks]] in [[Kyrgyzstan]].<ref name="Babak 2004 loc=252">{{Harvnb|Babak|Vaisman|Wasserman|2004|loc=252}}.</ref>
{| cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" width=250 align="right" rules="all" style="margin: 1em; background: #ffffff; border: 2px solid #aaa; font-size: 100%;" |- bgcolor=#DDDDDD | colspan=8 align="center" | Turks in Kyrgyzstan according to [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] Censuses and 1999, 2009 National Censuses<ref name="NewCensus">{{Citation| last =| first =| author-link =| last2 =| first2 =| author2-link =| title =Population and Housing Census 2009. Book 2. Part 1. (in tables). Population of Kyrgyzstan. (Перепись населения и жилищного фонда Кыргызской Республики 2009. Книга 2. Часть 1. (в таблицах). Население Кыргызстана)| place =Bishkek| publisher =National Committee on Statistics| origyear =| year =2010| month =| volume =| edition =| chapter =| chapterurl =| page =| pages =| url =http://212.42.101.100:8088/nacstat/sites/default/files/3.1.pdf| deadurl =yes| archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20110530011450/http://212.42.101.100:8088/nacstat/sites/default/files/3.1.pdf| archivedate =2011-05-30| df =}}</ref> |- bgcolor=#f0f0f0 align="center" ! Year ! Population |- | 1970 || 3,076 |- | 1979 || 5,160 |- | 1989 || 21,294 |- | 1999 || 33,327 |- | 2009 || 39,133 |}
== Demographics == [[Turkish people|Turks]] in Kyrgyzstan are often called ''Fergana Turks'' due to their large presence in the [[Fergana valley]].<ref>{{Harvnb|Minahan|1998 |loc=142}}.</ref>
== Education == The ''Kyrgyz-Turkish Manas University'' was established in Jal district of [[Bishkek]] in 1995 and has around 2,000 students. It is one of the leading universities in the country. The ''Kyrgyz-Turkish Anatolian High School'', ''Krygyz-Turkish Anatolian Girls Vocational School'', ''Bishkek Turkish Primary School'' and ''Turkish Language Teaching Center'' are run by the Turkish Ministry of Education.
