{{Unreferenced|date=November 2012}} {{Economic systems sidebar}}
An '''unplanned economy''' is an economy where economic decisions regarding production, investment and resource allocation are not linked together through conscious [[economic planning]]. This may refer to [[Subsistence economy|subsistence-level economies]], systems of [[barter]] or to more complex arrangements such as [[market economies]], and hypothetical systems such as [[Self-managed economy|self-managed]], distributed and [[network economies]]. Note that there may be a significant amount of planning within firms in market and [[Mixed economy|mixed-market]] economies.
== See also == *[[Economic planning]] *[[Economic system]] *[[Gift economy]] *[[Subsistence economy|Hunter-gatherer economy]] *[[Market economy]] *[[Mixed economy]] *[[Self-managed economy]]
